verses.roman:
skandhera upare bahu śākhā upajila
upari upari śākhā asaṅkhya ha-ila

synonyms: skandhera upare—upon the trunk; bahu śākhā—many branches; upajila—grew; upari upari—over and above them; śākhā—other branches; asaṅkhya—innumerable; ha-ila—fructified.
translation: From the trunk grew many branches and above them innumerable others.
